    {
      "id": "overview",
      "title": "Role Overview",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "Security Engineer interviews assess your knowledge of security principles, threat modeling, and ability to secure systems across the stack. Expect technical deep dives, scenario-based questions, and discussions about security culture."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "**What interviewers assess:**\n\n- Security fundamentals and best practices\n- Threat modeling and risk assessment\n- Application and infrastructure security\n- Incident response experience\n- Security tooling and automation"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "format",
      "title": "Common Interview Format",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "**Typical security interview loop:**\n\n1. **Recruiter screen** (30 min)\n2. **Technical phone screen** (60 min) - Security concepts or coding\n3. **Onsite/Virtual loop** (4-5 hours):\n   - Security architecture/design round\n   - Threat modeling exercise\n   - Coding/automation round\n   - Incident response scenario\n   - Behavioral round"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "tip",
          "content": {
            "text": "Security interviews often include 'How would you attack X?' questions. Show you can think like an attacker while maintaining ethical boundaries."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
